subject: Re: [junit] Need help
msgSnippet: ... Looks as though JUnit is not in your path when you run, although it is in your compile path.
messageBody:
On Wed, 29 Sep 2004 16:03:07 -0000, padalar <padalar@...> wrote:
> Hello,
>
> I am getting the following error whenever I run Junit tests using
> Ant1.6.1. Junit.jar version I am using the latest one.
>
> java.lang.NoSuchMethodError: junit.framework.Assert.assertEquals
> (Ljava/lang/String;Ljava/lang/String;Ljava/lang/String;)V

Looks as though JUnit is not in your path when you run, although it is
in your compile path.
